{"items":[{"tags":["oauth","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":18,"user_id":2174166,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c247fc8c8d6f98b4ded0ab4ea1fea92a?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"John Held","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/2174166/john-held"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":4802,"accepted_answer_id":15438212,"answer_count":1,"score":2,"last_activity_date":1506940020,"creation_date":1363365070,"last_edit_date":1506940020,"question_id":15437525,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15437525/box-api-oauth2-acces-token-request-error-invalid-grant-type-parameter-or-parame","title":"Box.api oauth2 acces token request error &quot;Invalid grant_type parameter or parameter missing&quot; when using POSTMAN","body":"<p>The documentation (<a href="http://developers.box.com/oauth/" rel="nofollow noreferrer">http://developers.box.com/oauth/</a>) suggests using POSTMAN or curl. </p>

<p>in this example, the clientID is 123, secret code is 456 and so on.</p>

<p>I am using Postman. 
In a prior step, I have obtained an access code via:
<a href="https://www.box.com/api/oauth2/authorize?response_type=code&amp;client_id=123" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://www.box.com/api/oauth2/authorize?response_type=code&amp;client_id=123</a>
let's say the response is xyz</p>

<p>In the next step, I use POSTMAN to issue a POST command (urlencoded)
<a href="https://www.box.com/api/oauth2/token?grant_type=authorization_code&amp;client_id=123&amp;client_secret=456&amp;code=xyz" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://www.box.com/api/oauth2/token?grant_type=authorization_code&amp;client_id=123&amp;client_secret=456&amp;code=xyz</a> </p>

<p>I do all of this within 30 seconds of obtaining the code in step 1.</p>

<p>The error is {"error":"invalid_request","error_description":"Invalid grant_type parameter or parameter missing"}</p>

<p>Alternatives I've tried: adding a redirect_uri, adding a response_type, only encoding the body with %D~% brackets. </p>

<p>I notice at least 5 similar questions for Box on stackoverflow, none with acknowledged solutions, though none with POSTMAN (which the documentation suggests).  </p>

<p>What is the resolution for obtaining an access token via POSTMAN for the BOX API?</p>
"},{"tags":["c#","box-api","box"],"owner":{"reputation":921,"user_id":738162,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":92,"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fb54b5ecd3bc7c87910d079b9f8b2189?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"Koby Mizrahy","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/738162/koby-mizrahy"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":401,"answer_count":2,"score":2,"last_activity_date":1467894728,"creation_date":1465288569,"question_id":37674381,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/37674381/box-add-collaboration-to-a-folder-using-appuser-user-token","title":"BOX: Add Collaboration to a folder using AppUser user token","body":"<p>I am building an integration between my organization back-end systems and BOX.</p>

<p>One of the scenarios is that when certain event is happening inside my organization there is a need to create a folder in BOX and add collaboration objects to that folder (connect groups to the folder).</p>

<p>I have no problem to create the folder but when trying to create the collaboration I am getting the following error: </p>

<p><strong>Box.V2.Exceptions.BoxException: Bearer realm="Service", error="insufficient_scope", error_description="The request requires higher privileges than provided by the access token."</strong></p>

<p>I am using BOX SDK for .Net to interact with BOX.</p>

<p>The application I created in BOX is assigned to use AppUser User Type and I provided all the scopes that BOX allows me (All scopes except "Manage enterprise" which is disabled).</p>

<p>The code that fails is (C#):</p>

<pre><code>var privateKey = File.ReadAllText(Settings.JwtPrivateKeyFile);
var boxConfig = new BoxConfig(Settings.ClientID, Settings.ClientSecret, Settings.EnterpriseID, privateKey, Settings.JwtPrivateKeyPassword, Settings.JwtPublicKeyID);
var jwt = BoxJWTAuth(boxConfig);
var token = jwt.AdminToken();
var client = jwt.AdminClient(token);

var addRequest = new BoxCollaborationRequest(){
    Item = new BoxRequestEntity() {
       Id = folderId,
       Type = BoxType.folder
    },
    AccessibleBy = new BoxCollaborationUserRequest(){
       Type = BoxType.@group,
       Id = groupId
    },
    Role = "viewer"
}; 
var api = client.CollaborationsManager;
var task = api.AddCollaborationAsync(addRequest);
task.Wait();
</code></pre>

<p>When running this code but replacing the Admin Token with Developer Token generated from the Box Applicaiton Edit Page it works.</p>

<p>Any help is appreciated</p>
"},{"tags":["php","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":16,"user_id":5055167,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":33,"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/73c0209d9bee9ec2ebab2c24dcf90953?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","display_name":"raman","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/5055167/raman"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":576,"answer_count":1,"score":2,"last_activity_date":1450093732,"creation_date":1450089836,"last_edit_date":1450093191,"question_id":34265018,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/34265018/box-com-file-uploading-in-php","title":"Box.com File Uploading in php","body":"<p>I am integrating Box.com Api to upload files from my website. </p>

