"},{"tags":["c#","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":13,"user_id":3546812,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1c32b16ab4b4fd98cd922e2305b6a3dd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","display_name":"user3546812","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/3546812/user3546812"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":338,"accepted_answer_id":34030593,"answer_count":1,"score":2,"last_activity_date":1449005546,"creation_date":1447998990,"question_id":33819919,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/33819919/box-file-upload-not-setting-content-created-at-attribute-c","title":"Box File upload not setting content_created_at attribute c#","body":"<p>I want to be able to set the content_created_at attribute when I upload a file and for some reason I can't get it to set. The file uploads just fine to the correct location, correct name, but the content_created_at doesn't get set. Any thoughts?</p>

<p>Here is the code that is uploading the file.</p>

<pre><code>      try
        {
            // Build URL
            string service = "https://upload.box.com/api/2.0/files/";
            string strContent = "content";
            string urlStr = service + strContent;

            // File and form data together
            //  - Because our base is .NET 4, we have to manually put together the request.  It's ugly but it works.
            HttpWebRequest request = (HttpWebRequest)WebRequest.Create(urlStr);
            request.Credentials = CredentialCache.DefaultCredentials;
            request.Method = "POST";
            request.Headers.Add("Authorization", "Bearer " + accessToken);
