"},{"tags":["box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":97,"user_id":1827106,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":40,"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Eoc6K.png?s=128&g=1","display_name":"JointEffort","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/1827106/jointeffort"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":272,"accepted_answer_id":13403276,"answer_count":1,"score":1,"last_activity_date":1353001814,"creation_date":1352997133,"question_id":13402004,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13402004/box-api-unauthorized-error-after-ticket-auth","title":"Box.api &#39;unauthorized&#39; error after ticket &amp; auth?","body":"<p>I followed the Box.com API manual at <a href="http://developers.box.com/get-started/#authenticating" rel="nofollow">http://developers.box.com/get-started/#authenticating</a> but still have a problem. I'm always getting the 'unauthorized' response. Do I need to redirect the user every time to the ticket URL? Or can I in my app reuse the auth token as long as the user doesn't reject my app?</p>

