<p>I'd like to be able to transfer "Inactive" user content to another Inactive user.</p>

<p>Today, when someone in our org separates, we have a script that automatically transfers their account data to the Box Admin account.  This has the side-effect of "re-enabling" collaboration on that data which makes assessing its candidacy for permanent deletion murkier.  Instead, I'd like to transfer the content to a generic service account which itself is inactive.  This will ensure the content is still around, but unavailable for collaboration which should prompt feedback from anyone still needing it.</p>

<p>Will give it a try and share if it works or not.  Worst case, I can have our script re-enable the account temporarily I suppose?</p>
