"},{"tags":["authentication","notifications","http-headers","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":1,"user_id":2361678,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f86062fb1d035d17b798e411e820f64f?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"user2361678","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/2361678/user2361678"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":50,"answer_count":1,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1368320487,"creation_date":1368165786,"last_edit_date":1368195650,"question_id":16476138,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/16476138/how-to-add-authentication-to-event-notification","title":"How to add authentication to Event Notification?","body":"<p>I looked through documentation on Event Notification (<a href="http://developers.box.com/webhooks/" rel="nofollow">http://developers.box.com/webhooks/</a>).</p>

<p>I would like to call an REST API, with basic authentication. Is there a way to do this?</p>

