<p>So if a user created a folder, as part of "created" event notification, in addition to user-id and user's name, I've a need to know user's source IP address.</p>
"},{"tags":["box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":1,"user_id":1493101,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8ef756f4e5e5131231345ebb06b22938?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"jon","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/1493101/jon"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":584,"answer_count":1,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1362871615,"creation_date":1362752647,"question_id":15296171,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15296171/access-token-expires-during-upload","title":"Access token expires during upload","body":"<p>I'm running into a problem with I think is an access token expiring in the middle of an upload. For example, if I currently have a valid (just refreshed) access token, then run:</p>

<pre><code>curl -vS --limit-rate 30K 'https://api.box.com/2.0/files/content' -H 'Authorization: Bearer VALID_ACCESS_TOKEN' -F filename=@/tmp/example.zip -F folder_id=12345
</code></pre>

<p>Which takes more than an hour to upload, I eventually get this in the end:</p>

<pre><code>&lt; HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
...
&lt; WWW-Authenticate: Bearer realm="Service", error="invalid_token", error_description="The access token provided is invalid."
...
* HTTP error before end of send, stop sending
</code></pre>

<p>The files I tested are big, but still within the 250MB upload limit.</p>

<p>Does anyone have any ideas what to do about this problem?</p>
"},{"tags":["ruby-on-rails","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":1102,"user_id":340616,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":84,"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/00e6f6ca5230ea92fb392bb46b3ee683?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"alex","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/340616/alex"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":839,"accepted_answer_id":14699099,"answer_count":2,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1360030642,"creation_date":1360020856,"last_edit_date":1360023683,"question_id":14697705,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/14697705/equivalent-of-curl-post-request-call-in-rails-model-or-controller","title":"Equivalent of cURL Post request call in rails model or controller","body":"<p>The following line of code works fine when I call it from the terminal. I want to run the equivalent of it from within my Rails app to refresh my access_token field (see <a href="http://developers.box.com/oauth/" rel="nofollow">Using the Access and Refresh Tokens</a>):</p>

<pre><code>curl https://api.box.com/oauth2/token \
-d 'grant_type=refresh_token&amp;refresh_token={valid refresh token}&amp;client_id={your_client_id}&amp;client_secret={your_client_secret}' \
-X POST
</code></pre>

<p>Assuming I have all the params available, how would I post this request from a model or controller?</p>
"},{"tags":["ios","sdk","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":78,"user_id":888615,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":100,"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/61e996dc241881bc2779296050c2935d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","display_name":"kp_","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/888615/kp"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":602,"accepted_answer_id":14016104,"answer_count":1,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1356312413,"creation_date":1356219943,"last_edit_date":1356244978,"question_id":14007543,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/14007543/box-net-ios-sdk-moving-files-and-folders","title":"Box.Net iOS SDK Moving Files and Folders","body":"<p>I am currently developing an iOS application and am implementing the Box.Net SDK. I have gotten everything to work except the ability to move files around, which is not a native feature of the SDK. I am trying to twist my way through it. </p>

<p>If you are familiar with the structure of Box.Net, each file/folder has an ID number for itself, and an ID its parent. From what I understand if I want to move a file, I am supposed to change the parent ID number on the file which will point it to the new location. I can't seem to get it to work properly though. My application seems to keep crashing.</p>

<p>This is what I have so far, generalized. </p>

<pre><code>BoxObject *boxObject = [[[Box objectWithID:(ID#ofParent)] children] objectAtIndex:i];
[boxObject parent].boxID = 0; // &lt;-- Problem (causes crash)
</code></pre>

<p>I also tried this.</p>

<pre><code>[boxObject setParent:[Box folderWithID:[BoxID numberWithInt:i]]];
</code></pre>

<p>The boxObject variable is the file that I want to move. I am setting its parent ID equal to 0, which is supposed to be the root folder. However, my application crashes when I try to reassign the parent ID for the file. Any ideas on how to successfully move files/folders? Any help is much appreciated! Thanks in advance!  </p>
"},{"tags":["node.js","http","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":2269,"user_id":375847,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":95,"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/cdb3241e99ee754525fc8d976382ad21?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"giodamelio","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/375847/giodamelio"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":253,"accepted_answer_id":13789207,"answer_count":1,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1355069962,"creation_date":1355066903,"question_id":13788804,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13788804/box-api-irregular-headers","title":"Box API Irregular Headers","body":"<p>I am trying to upload an image with the box API and the <a href="https://github.com/mikeal/request" rel="nofollow"><code>request module</code></a>. I tried the provided curl example without any problems.</p>

<p>I have a request all setup like this</p>

<pre><code>var request = require("request");
var fs = require("fs");
var path = require("path");

request({
    url: "https://api.box.com/2.0/files/content",
    method: "POST",
    form: {
        filename: fs.createReadStream(path.join(__dirname, "midguts.jpg")),
        folder_id: "0"
    },
    headers: {
        api_key: "&lt;API_KEY&gt;",
        auth_token: "&lt;AUTH_TOKEN&gt;"
    }
}, function (error, response, body) {
    console.log(error);
    console.log(body);
});
</code></pre>

<p>The problem arises when I get to the headers part. The <a href="http://developers.box.com/docs/#files-upload-a-file" rel="nofollow"><code>box API</code></a> call for a headers string of</p>

<pre><code>"Authorization: BoxAuth api_key=API_KEY&amp;auth_token=AUTH_TOKEN"
</code></pre>

<p>but I with the request module I can only send an object of key, value pairs. I also looked at the docs for nodes <a href="http://nodejs.org/api/http.html#http_http_request_options_callback" rel="nofollow"><code>http.request</code></a> and found it has the same issue.</p>

<p>So the question is, why does the API not follow the standard key pair format and how can I send a POST request that will work?</p>
"},{"tags":["box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":37,"user_id":848291,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":60,"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1ab967a68edfb8f96a40ec04a7bac12d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"Brook","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/848291/brook"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":1349,"answer_count":2,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1354377480,"creation_date":1353976848,"question_id":13575657,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13575657/simple-application-to-support-uploads-to-box-com","title":"Simple Application to support uploads to box.com","body":"<p>I am trying to create a simple box.com application that will support folder creation and file uploads from our application to box.com for use by multiple box.com users.</p>

<p>I have a couple of questions:</p>

<ol>
<li><p>For testing, I create a new application and specified that I did not want it to be public (while we develop it). But I can't add it to my test user account because I can't find it - so how can I test it? How do I add it to my end user box.com account?</p></li>
<li><p>The idea is to have the box.com user enter their credentials or key or something in our software so that we can automate the uploading of files and creation of folders within their accounts. But everything I read talks about getting a ticket and redirecting the user to a login page. We need to automate this process so we can upload files/create folders without the box.com users present. How is this done?</p></li>
</ol>
"},{"tags":["box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":11,"user_id":1627577,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":0,"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/71821fd33bcdedca7582320ebc01ea34?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"OKE","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/1627577/oke"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":166,"answer_count":1,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1352407453,"creation_date":1352391921,"question_id":13293210,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13293210/can-a-web-link-be-shared-with-api-v2-0","title":"Can a web_link be shared with API v2.0?","body":"<p>You can create a web_link file on a Box Folder.
The web_link can be shared via Box UI, but I could not do it with API v2.0:</p>

<p>Neither: <br/>
<strong>PUT /files/{file id}</strong>              nor<br/>
<strong>PUT /web_links/{file id}</strong><br/>
worked. Both returned HTTP 404 when used with the id of the web_link.</p>

<p>Is this supported or am I missing something?</p>
"},{"tags":["box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":15,"user_id":1471813,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/24fb1b9d10a0ecada5bc042e0a5c29ea?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"O. V.","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/1471813/o-v"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":193,"answer_count":0,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1352737016,"creation_date":1351175424,"question_id":13070873,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13070873/box-api-download-a-file-how-to-save-raw-text-response-to-file-with-correct-enco","title":"box-api Download a File: how to save raw text response to file with correct encoding","body":"<p>I implemented downloading a file. I received raw string data. I save this data to a file, but can't open it, because file is invalid.</p>

<p>I tried to download jpg image.
I think this is a result of incorrect converting this data to bytes.</p>

<p>What Encoding I need to use?</p>
"},{"tags":["authentication","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":3,"user_id":773938,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d6e0e791e94e03506c2723a97dc38066?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"Zak Mandhro","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/773938/zak-mandhro"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":90,"accepted_answer_id":12696144,"answer_count":1,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1349351659,"creation_date":1349197626,"last_edit_date":1349351659,"question_id":12694938,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12694938/how-to-authenticate-user-coming-from-file-action","title":"How to authenticate user coming from File Action","body":"<p>Is there a way to authenticate a user coming from a <strong>File Action</strong> without requiring ticket-> redirect->token?</p>

<p>Here's the scenario:</p>

<ol>
<li>User adds our web app to their account on Box.com web site</li>
<li>User selects a file clicks on "Open with Our App" (File Actions - Popup)</li>
<li>Our app receives the parameters for file URL, file auth token, etc.</li>
<li>User wishes to add comment to the file from our app</li>
</ol>

<p>How do we make API call to add comment to file? Throughout the flow above, we do no have a user auth token required for API calls, even though user added the app and interacted with it.</p>

<p>Thanks for the help!</p>
"},{"tags":["box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":628,"user_id":824160,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":55,"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d2a5cdd34483a7695df1969ba865aa6f?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"Robert Grezan","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/824160/robert-grezan"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":291,"accepted_answer_id":12659070,"answer_count":2,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1349034393,"creation_date":1348892501,"question_id":12649882,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12649882/box-api-v2-feedback-folders-response-should-have-at-least-some-information-ab","title":"Box api v2 feedback: â€œfoldersâ€ response should have at least some information about files","body":"<p>This is feedback based on Box.net comment on developer page asking for v2 feedback.</p>

<p>What the api currently returns for each folder "entry" is something like:</p>

<pre><code>"entries" : 
[
    {
        "sequence_id": "0",
        "type": "file",
        "id": "2631999573",
        "name":"IMG_1312.JPG"
    },
    {
        "type":"folder",
        "id":"2305623799",
        "sequence_id":"1",
        "name":"a child folder"
    }
]
</code></pre>

<p>This means that to retrieve basic metadata (size, modification date etc) for a child entry I have to issue a REST request for each item. This is clearly very inefficient.</p>

<p>The question is: is there any chance that this will be changed in before v2 is released?</p>
"},{"tags":["box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":308,"user_id":906366,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":97,"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/990bae82d4819fa3ed40a0807a4d0896?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"benkdev","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/906366/benkdev"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":96,"accepted_answer_id":12188201,"answer_count":1,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1346285351,"creation_date":1346263340,"question_id":12183867,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12183867/box-how-to-tell-if-the-root-folder-has-been-modified","title":"Box - how to tell if the root folder has been modified?","body":"<p>I noticed that the call to <a href="https://api.box.com/2.0/folders/0.xml" rel="nofollow">https://api.box.com/2.0/folders/0.xml</a> does not return a modified-at tag.  How can I tell when the root folder has been modified?</p>

<p>A solution I came up with is to check the folders directly beneath the root folder for modified-at dates.  However, that could result in a significant amount of HTTP calls.</p>

<p>Is there a better way?</p>
"},{"tags":["box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":1,"user_id":1630614,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3a11c59ebea8c34e9c1e264454497e1c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"Travis Buffington","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/1630614/travis-buffington"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":170,"answer_count":1,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1346188886,"creation_date":1346165241,"question_id":12161891,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12161891/box-net-api-v2-0-moving-file-on-service-action","title":"Box.Net API v2.0 Moving File on Service Action","body":"<p>Building a workflow that allows a file to be dynamically moved via user input (renames, the whole works). Using the Service Action, a web service will rename and move the file based on user input fields and some other behind the scenes processing. However, once the service runs and the window closes, the file is move but the user experience goes bad. The file keeps refreshing in the preview pane, redirects back to the root, and nothing works right until you navigate away.</p>

<p>The ideal solution would be the for the file to be moved and the user moved to the next file in the folder (or at minimum kept in the folder) as we're looking at a "processing" folder.</p>

<p>Is there any ideal best practice? Do I simply just need to copy the file instead of move and then run a delete routine after-the-fact?</p>
"},{"tags":["box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":13,"user_id":1555109,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/db096fe06f3e0b006ec3be05b3f10795?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"Gavin","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/1555109/gavin"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":624,"accepted_answer_id":12223759,"answer_count":2,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1346457360,"creation_date":1345919165,"question_id":12124563,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12124563/error-when-authenticating-box-app-with-enterprise-account-that-uses-sso","title":"Error when authenticating Box app with Enterprise account that uses SSO","body":"<p>I am developing an app against an Enterprise account that has SSO enabled.  When I authenticate, it will accept just my email address if I am already authenticated with Box in my browser session.  All looks good, and I get the message via Box "Thanks for logging in"...and that I am free to proceed with my app.</p>

<p>However, when I try to get my auth token, I get the "get_auth_token_error", and the Box documentation doesn't give me any details on this, other than saying it is a generic error state.</p>

<p>I've tested this with a non-enterprise app (which obviously is not SSO), and all works.  Note I am v1 of the Box API</p>
"},{"tags":["paging","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":8,"user_id":1614811,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b282e2148cf54ddd8b8793e442c99993?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"Matt Butler","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/1614811/matt-butler"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":139,"answer_count":1,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1347986585,"creation_date":1345567382,"last_edit_date":1347986585,"question_id":12059432,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12059432/are-there-paging-mechanisms-in-the-box-v2-api","title":"Are there paging mechanisms in the box v2 API?","body":"<p>I'm looking at the APIs for things like <a href="http://developers.box.com/docs/#folders-retrieve-a-folders-items" rel="nofollow">retrieve a folder's items</a> and <a href="http://developers.box.com/docs/#dicussions-retrieve-the-discussions-comments" rel="nofollow">retrieve the discussion's comments</a> and I don't see any paging mechanisms. </p>

<p>Am I missing something, or is there a reason why they aren't there ?</p>
"},{"tags":["ruby","curl","oauth","rest-client","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":939,"user_id":211780,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":50,"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/cb7758ca073164628a3a078164119865?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"Pyro2927","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/211780/pyro2927"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":1303,"accepted_answer_id":11926722,"answer_count":1,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1344815021,"creation_date":1344811057,"question_id":11926406,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11926406/ruby-multi-part-form-upload-with-restclient","title":"Ruby Multi-part Form Upload with RestClient","body":"<p>I'm working on a ruby application, and am trying to upload a file to box.net.  I have it working with the curl call</p>

<pre><code>curl https://www.box.com/api/2.0/files/data -H "Authorization: BoxAuth api_key=&lt;API_KEY&gt;&amp;auth_token=&lt;AUTH_TOKEN&gt;" -F folder_id=0 -F filename=@test.txt --trace ~/Desktop/log.txt
</code></pre>

<p>I've tried to translate this into ruby, and have tried the following</p>

<pre><code>request = RestClient::Request.new(:method =&gt; :post,:url =&gt; "https://www.box.com/api/2.0/files/data",:authorization =&gt; "BoxAuth api_key=&lt;API_KEY&gt;&amp;auth_token=&lt;AUTH_TOKEN&gt;",:filename =&gt; "test.txt", :payload =&gt; { :multipart =&gt; true, :file =&gt; File.new("test.txt"))
request.execute
</code></pre>

<p>but I keep getting back a "401: Unauthorized" response.  I've also tried using the box-api gem, but that seems to only work with version 1.0 of the API, and I'm trying to interface with 2.0.</p>
"},{"tags":["java","authentication","single-sign-on","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":8,"user_id":339202,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/7574a661eb50f532f87a25e7c6d6bad5?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"Assaf","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/339202/assaf"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":165,"answer_count":1,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1344891246,"creation_date":1344776786,"last_edit_date":1344778145,"question_id":11922407,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11922407/api-for-direct-login","title":"api for direct login","body":"<p>I am developing a java app for admin users in an organization.
The admin user has access to the organization main box folder.
I want my application to sign in the admin directly (without having to type his username and password in your box login site)</p>

