"},{"tags":["python","api","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":532,"user_id":2646813,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":76,"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5176062727191b19931e72a973715379?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"nlr25","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/2646813/nlr25"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":126,"accepted_answer_id":20340880,"answer_count":2,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1387407487,"creation_date":1386029404,"question_id":20340388,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/20340388/grabbing-http-get-parameter-from-url-using-box-api-in-python","title":"grabbing HTTP GET parameter from url using Box API in python","body":"<p>I am dealing with the Box.com API using python and am having some trouble automating a step in the authentication process.</p>

