"},{"tags":["python","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":2276,"user_id":1373934,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3ccacf24c4f98c47c5346f6d09135d9c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"brettcvz","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/1373934/brettcvz"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":479,"answer_count":0,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1349151789,"creation_date":1349126732,"question_id":12681345,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12681345/box-timeout-on-uploading-of-very-large-file","title":"Box timeout on uploading of very large file","body":"<p>We are trying to upload very large (+1Gb) files to Box via the upload api using python's httplib.</p>

<p>So that we don't have to keep the whole file in memory, we are using code like:</p>

<pre><code>CHUNK_SIZE = 1024 * 1024
