"},{"tags":["box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":48,"user_id":1301016,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/47443a2562d89ff8b1bb53a4e8477f88?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"simon","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/1301016/simon"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":135,"answer_count":1,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1402442389,"creation_date":1402046504,"question_id":24078340,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/24078340/oauth-for-enterprise-account","title":"OAuth for Enterprise account","body":"<p>I'm creating a web app for my company that will keep a number of files in sync with the files on Box. This will be done by using a cron job running every hour.</p>

<p>I have the application working by setting the developer token in my account, this was done for testing whilst I was building the application.</p>

<p>Now this is working I want to get the authentication working so I can just leaving this running. So I'm trying to work out if there is a way I can have an API key for our enterprise account or if I will have to implement OAuth and connect one user to the application, which seems to be a bit overkill?</p>
"},{"tags":["file","https","upload","box-api","box"],"owner":{"reputation":44,"user_id":1563137,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4527dc8f62a08c0417c76232963780fe?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"Chris","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/1563137/chris"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":89,"answer_count":0,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1401825233,"creation_date":1401810074,"last_edit_date":1401825233,"question_id":24019355,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/24019355/post-file-directly-to-box-no-oauth","title":"Post file directly to Box - no OAuth","body":"<p>Good day -</p>

<p>Our enterprise uses Box for cloud storage.  There are many intranet web applications behind our firewall <em>that do not use HTTPS</em>.  </p>

<p>When a user uses one of these web applications, it's easy for the app to <strong>retrieve</strong> files for processing: we just use the Box Picker and the user performs the authorization, which then sends the file token to our app.  Then we retrieve the file securely from Box to our server.</p>

<p>But what if our application generates a file for the user, and we want to give the user a quick way to <strong>upload</strong> it to Box?  Today, we would have to use OAuth, which generates a callback that has to be to HTTPS.  That's not a workable solution because we don't have SSL on some intranet servers.</p>

<p>Is there a way to let the user "POST" this file directly to Box from the browser?</p>

<p>For example:</p>

<pre><code>&lt;form method="POST" action="**https://www.box.com**...." type="multipart.."&gt;
    &lt;input type="hidden name="fileContent" value="base64 encoded file content"&gt;&lt;/input&gt;\
    &lt;input type="hidden name="fileNname" value="...."&gt;&lt;/input&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>This way, our server "passes off" the file to Box, which then performs authentication as needed, and proceeds with putting it in the user's account.  It would not require a secure callback to our server at all.  Of course, this POST is via HTTPS to Box.</p>

<p>Is there any way to do this without needing OAuth?</p>

<p>Thank you.</p>
"},{"tags":["box-api","box"],"owner":{"reputation":1,"user_id":3664371,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/gRah3.jpg?s=128&g=1","display_name":"Palanisamy Ramasamy","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/3664371/palanisamy-ramasamy"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":145,"answer_count":0,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1400756371,"creation_date":1400754911,"last_edit_date":1400756371,"question_id":23804389,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/23804389/how-to-add-task-using-the-box-java-sdk-v2-for-a-file","title":"How to add task using the box-java-sdk-v2 for a file?","body":"<p>When I am searching a solution for assign tasks to a file in box-java-sdk-v2, I only get four lines of search results in the box-java-sdk-v2. </p>

<p>But i didn't find any solution for add task. </p>

<p>Box team please advise me: is it possible to create or add task in box-java-sdk-v2?</p>
"},{"tags":["javascript","jquery","ajax","oauth-2.0","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":11,"user_id":3605985,"user_type":"registered","profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b7cedabf00e67f2686e962a745d25e1b?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","display_name":"the_danimal","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/3605985/the-danimal"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":3984,"answer_count":1,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1402943834,"creation_date":1399327621,"question_id":23482705,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/23482705/connecting-via-oauth2-with-jquery-ajax-for-box-com","title":"Connecting via oAuth2 with jQuery/AJAX for Box.com","body":"<p>I'm trying to work with Box.com's API to develop a quick app that allows for Folder creation. I am having trouble connecting to their API and am fairly new to oAUTH2, API's, and whatnot. I've tried to follow these guides:</p>

<p><a href="http://developers.box.com/oauth/" rel="nofollow">http://developers.box.com/oauth/</a></p>

<p><a href="http://developers.box.com/docs/#folders-create-a-new-folder" rel="nofollow">http://developers.box.com/docs/#folders-create-a-new-folder</a></p>

<p>The Box.com documentation says</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>response_type: Whether the endpoint returns an authorization code. For
  web applications, a value of code should be used.</p>

  <p>client_id : The client_id you obtained in the Initial Setup.</p>

  <p>redirect_uri :An HTTPS URI or custom URL scheme where the response
  will be redirected. Optional if the redirect URI is registered with
  Box already. </p>

  <p>state :    An arbitrary string of your choosing that will be
  included in the response to your application. Box recommends that you
  use an anti-forgery state token to prevent CSRF attacks to your users</p>

  <p>A sample GET request could therefore look like:</p>

  <p>GET
  https: //www.box.com/api/oauth2/authorize?response_type=code&amp;client_id=MY_CLIENT_ID&amp;state=security_token%3DKnhMJatFipTAnM0nHlZA</p>
</blockquote>

<p>I have a dev account with them and here is my basic jquery that is not working..</p>

<pre><code> $.ajax({
  //The URL to process the request
    url : 'https://www.box.com/api/oauth2/authorize',
    type : 'GET',
    data : {
      response_type : 'code',
      client_id : 'm025a55gtov17txux1v2vbzjjhph2b6n'
    },
  success: function( resp ) {
    console.log( resp.people );
  },
  error: function( req, status, err ) {
    console.log( 'something went wrong', status, err );}

  });
</code></pre>

<p>Can anyone point me in the direction on how to do this? I'm stumped.</p>
"},{"tags":["oauth-2.0","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":416,"user_id":2979306,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":48,"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/70f2a7303c63270b02d3494b3825ea63?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","display_name":"RikyTres","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/2979306/rikytres"},"is_answered":true,"view_count":558,"answer_count":2,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1398172523,"creation_date":1397556159,"last_edit_date":1397633919,"question_id":23080505,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/23080505/insecure-redirect-uri-error-on-my-box-app-on-authentication","title":"&quot;Insecure_redirect_uri&quot; error on my Box App on authentication","body":"<p>I'm try to test my app, and I'm testing it both on localhost and on heroku.</p>

<p>I try to not set a <code>redirect_uri</code> in the "OAuth2 Parameters" on my app's edit page, so I thought I will be able to set it dynamically depending of the host name (localhost:port or myapp.heroku.com)</p>

<p>But this doesn't work... Am I doing something wrong?</p>

<hr>

<h1>Edit</h1>

<p>Problem should be the protocol for the authentication. </p>

