<p>Can anything be done to improve the performance, or is that a typical response time?  I noticed when using the Box website (see below), it appears much quicker 2-3 seconds.</p>

<p><a href="https://app.box.com/folder/0/search?query=fees&amp;pageSize=20&amp;sortDirection=desc&amp;types=pdf&amp;kinds=file_content&amp;metadata=&amp;folderID=0" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://app.box.com/folder/0/search?query=fees&amp;pageSize=20&amp;sortDirection=desc&amp;types=pdf&amp;kinds=file_content&amp;metadata=&amp;folderID=0</a></p>

<p>In addition, in the website search results there is an extract with highlighting, is that possible through the API?  Is there a field that can be requested with this information?</p>

<p><strong>EDIT</strong> - I was was able to improve the time slightly by using the fields parameter, but it was still 4-5 seconds to retrieve the first 200 matches.</p>

<p>fields=name,size,path_collection,created_at,modified_at </p>
"},{"tags":["objective-c","box-api"],"owner":{"reputation":481,"user_id":1086644,"user_type":"registered","accept_rate":58,"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a58e13526a2dc520a5a20a0295cd90ae?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","display_name":"NOP","link":"https://stackoverflow.com/users/1086644/nop"},"is_answered":false,"view_count":43,"answer_count":0,"score":0,"last_activity_date":1481403904,"creation_date":1481400437,"last_edit_date":1481403904,"question_id":41079778,"link":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41079778/ios-box-api-wait-for-request-to-finish","title":"iOS Box API - wait for request to finish","body":"<p>Is there a way to wait for the Box API to finish all requests? So for example, if I make a folder item request, I would like to have my program wait for the completion handler to finish before moving on.</p>

